<preface>
  <title>Conventions</title>
  <para>The following conventions are used throughout this document.</para>
  <section>
    <title>Significant Keywords</title>
    <para>The key words 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">must</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">must not</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">required</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">shall</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">shall not</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">should</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">should not</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">recommended</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">not recommended</phrase>, 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">may</phrase>, and 
    <phrase role="rfc2119">optional</phrase> in this document are to be
    interpreted as described in 
    <citetitle pubwork="article">IETF RFC 2119</citetitle>
    <xref linkend="bib-RFC2119" />.</para>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Text Representations</title>
    <para>All strings and text found in the JXTA Protocols should be assumed
    to be encoded using Unicode 
    <xref linkend="bib-USA28" /> Canonical UTF8 (NFC) (see 
    <citetitle>Unicode Standard Annex #15 : Unicode Normalization
    Forms</citetitle>
    <xref linkend="bib-USA15" />) unless otherwise specified.</para>
  </section>
</preface>
